title: UMD Men Drop to No. 7 in USCHO Poll
text:
UMD Men Drop to No. 7 in USCHO Poll 
By Zach Schneider UMD Men Drop to No. 7 in USCHO Poll October 12, 2015 Updated Oct 12, 2015 at 3:20 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team dropped five spots to No. 7 in this week's United States College Hockey Online (USCHO) Division I poll, which was released on Monday morning. 
The Bulldogs dropped their season opener this past Saturday, losing 3-2 to Bemidji State on the road after the teams' scheduled Friday night game at AMSOIL Arena was postponed due to a power outage. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
For full results of this week's USCHO Division I men's poll, click here. 
UMD is (0-1-0) overall this season and will be playing a home-and-home series against No. 15 Minnesota this Friday and Saturday.
